metadata.name: she should be here
metadata.description:
ever been somewhere and thought…she/he/they should be here? what is that feeling? why do we think we know where someone “SHOULD” be…our own love can get so full, like a cloud on a rainy day, that sometimes, it’s best to let the storm wash over you.
•
most days i know that there’s nothing i can do to speed up time or crunch the distance between us until the next time i can see her. but sometimes it feels good to be vulnerable and honest with myself, while i know nobody ‘needs’ anyone, it’s feels nice to want to be with her and to be wanted in return. 
•
